```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "resource_requirements": {
      "walltime": "24:00:00",
      "cores": 1,
      "nodes": 1,
      "processors_per_task": 5
    },
    "job_name": "rs1",
    "output_file": "rs1-slurm.%N.%j.out",
    "error_file": "rs1-slurm.%N.%j.err",
    "software": [
      "python",
      "PyHipp",
      "DataProcessingTools",
      "aws",
      "sns"
    ]
  }
}
```

This script uses **SLURM** for job scheduling and resource allocation. It requests 1 core, 1 node, and 5 processors per task, with a 24-hour runtime limit. The script also uses Python libraries **PyHipp** and **DataProcessingTools** for data processing. It uses **AWS SNS** to send a notification when the job is complete.
